casebody.data:
WILLIAM ELLERBE et al. v. KARL C. J. HANSELMAN [No. 4,

October Term, 1939.]

Decided October 25th, 1939.

*683The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Offutt, Paeke, Sloan, Mitchell, Shehan, Johnson, and Delaplaine, JJ.

Hyman Ginsberg, with whom were Ginsberg & Ginsberg on the brief, for the appellants. M. William Adelson, with whom were Edtvin J. Dickerson and Dickerson, Nice & Sokol on the brief, for the appellee. Bond, C. J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
